SIMPLE: eyestone
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eyestone
<hw>Eye"stone`</hw> <pr>(⟦imac⟧"st⟦omac⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A small, lenticular, calcareous body, esp. an operculum
of a small marine shell of the family <fam>Turbinid⟦ae⟧</fam>, used to
remove a foreign substance from the eye. It is put into the inner corner
of the eye under the lid, and allowed to work its way out at the outer
corner, bringing with it the substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Eye agate. See under
<er>Eye</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eyestring</ent>⟦br⟧
